defaultKey Points:defaultBackgrounddefaultProfessor Marsden is the Director of the Institute for Transport Studies at the University of Leeds. He is also the Project Director for the Disruption project (
defaultwww.disruptionproject.net
default), a £1.2m Research Council study examining what can be learnt from disruptive events of various sorts. 
default 
defaultJeremy Shires is a Senior Research Fellow at the Institute for Transport Studies at University of Leeds and had responsibility for designing and implementing all surveys undertaken as part of the Disruption project.
default 
defaultThe Disruption project conducted a large scale on-line survey (
default2,417
default) in six of the worst affected areas of the UK (Hampshire, Kent, Surrey, Norfolk, South Wales and West Yorkshire) during the severe bout of winter weather in January 2013. The submission draws on the findings from this survey and broader insights from the Disruption project which has also explored flooding and infrastructure closure. The submission however represents
default the views of the authors 
defaultrather than the Disruption project team or the Institute for Transport Studies.
